Set up the basic CLI project structure for chipper in Go.

Language and libraries:
- Go (single static binary, no runtime dependencies)
- Cobra — subcommand routing and argument parsing
- Bubble Tea — interactive TUI (sorting, staging interface)
- Huh — interactive prompts (init, slug assignment, etc.)
- Lip Gloss — terminal styling

Project structure:
- cmd/ — one file per subcommand
- internal/ — manifest parsing, git operations, config
- main.go — entry point

Tasks:
- Initialize Go module (module path: github.com/user/chipper or similar)
- Add dependencies
- Wire up Cobra with all top-level subcommands as stubs
- Confirm `chipper --help` produces clean output
- `go install` installs the binary to $GOPATH/bin

This ticket is a prerequisite for all other implementation tickets.
